ng.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSo you would only use an IBOUTLET when you wanted to change the way something looked i.e the Label you use an outlet since you want to change it\'s text property you could change it\'s size, colour, font etc.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nYou would use an action when you want something to be triggered when the user presses something which in this case is changing the text in the label when you press the button you are using the action to activate a trigger event .\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nBasically the action is used when you want the app to do something and the IBOUTLET is used when you want to change the properties of a control which is on display on the screen.\r\n\r\n</div>','what is the difference between outlet and action','','publish','open','open','','what-is-the-difference-between-outlet-and-action','','','2014-12-18 22:28:18','2014-12-19 03:28:18','',0,'http://zhexiao.zz.mu/?p=205',0,'post','',0),(206,1,'2014-12-18 22:27:34','2014-12-19 03:27:34','<div><p>The&nbsp;IBOUTLET allows you to change properties of a control while the Action is used for an event to trigger code basically do something.&nbsp;</p><p>So you would only use an IBOUTLET when you wanted to change the way something looked i.e the Label you use an outlet since you want to change it\'s text property you could change it\'s size, colour, font etc.</p><p> You would use an action when you want something to be triggered when the user presses something which in this case is changing the text in the label when you press the button you are using the action to activate a trigger event .</p><p>Basically the action is used when you want the app to do something and the IBOUTLET is used when you want to change the properties of a control which is on display on the screen.<br></p></div>','what is the difference between outlet and action','','inherit','open','open','','205-revision-v1','','','2014-12-18 22:27:34','2014-12-19 03:27:34','',205,'http://zhexiao.zz.mu/205-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(207,1,'2014-12-18 22:28:18','2014-12-19 03:28:18','<div>\r\n\r\nThe IBOUTLET allows you to change properties of a control while the Action is used for an event to trigger code basically do something.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSo you would only use an IBOUTLET when you wanted to change the way something looked i.e the Label you use an outlet since you want to change it\'s text property you could change it\'s size, colour, font etc.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nYou would use an action when you want something to be triggered when the user presses something which in this case is changing the text in the label when you press the button you are using the action to activate a trigger event .\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nBasically the action is used when you want the app to do something and the IBOUTLET is used when you want to change the properties of a control which is on display on the screen.\r\n\r\n</div>','what is the difference between outlet and action','','inherit','open','open','','205-revision-v1','','','2014-12-18 22:28:18','2014-12-19 03:28:18','',205,'http://zhexiao.zz.mu/205-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(200,1,'2014-12-17 22:44:30','2014-12-18 03:44:30','','html5_wallpaper_1680x1050','','inherit','open','open','','html5_wallpaper_1680x1050','','','2014-12-17 22:44:30','2014-12-18 03:44:30','',12,'http://zhexiao.zz.mu/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/html5_wallpaper_1680x10501.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(201,1,'2014-12-17 23:02:40','2014-12-18 04:02:40','<div><p>This is a tutorial for teach you how to handle wordpress database connection error.</p><blockquote class=\"zocle_blockquote\" style=\"clear:both;\"><div class=\"zocle-editor-content\" data-og-id=\"1418875140400\" data-uniqid=\"1418875140400\" contenteditable=\"false\"><div class=\"sort-element-content\"><div class=\"Zocle_Content_Wrapper Zocle_RSS\"><div class=\"Zocle_Content_Image_Left\"><a title=\"How to Add a Custom Database Error Page in WordPress\" alt=\"How to Add a Custom Database Error Page in WordPress\" href=\"http://zocle.us/aI4w\" target=\"_blank\">			    						<img src=\"http://cdn4.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/customdberror.png\" class=\"rssShowImgSrc fr-fin\" data-num=\"1\">			    					</a></div><div class=\"Zocle_Content_Details\"><h2 class=\"Zocle_Content_Headline\"><a href=\"http://zocle.us/aI4w\" target=\"_blank\">How to Add a Custom Database Error Page in WordPress</a></h2><div class=\"Zocle_Content_URL\">Via&nbsp;wpbeg.in</div><div class=\"Zocle_Content_Teaser\">A simple tutorial that shows you how to customize your error establishing database connection or other database error pages in WordPress.</div><div class=\"Zocle_Content_Date\"><time>12/17/2014 10:53 PM</time></div></div></div></div></div></blockquote><p><br></p></div>','How to Add a Custom Database Error Page in WordPress','','publish','open','open','','how-to-add-a-custom-database-error-page-in-wordpress','','','2014-12-17 23:02:40','2014-12-18 04:02:40','',0,'http://zhexiao.zz.mu/?p=201',0,'post','',0),(56,1,'2014-11-25 18:15:00','2014-11-25 23:15:00','<div><p>How to Use ExpressJS with Node.js to Write Data to A MongoDB Database<br></p><blockquote class=\"zocle_blockquote\" style=\"clear:both;\"><div class=\"zocle-editor-content\"><div class=\"sort-element-content\"><div class=\"Zocle_Content_Wrapper Zocle_Twitter\"><div class=\"Zocle_Content_Image_Left\"><img src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/505048043377262592/VMUR5EzE_normal.png\" class=\"fr-fin\"></div><div class=\"Zocle_Content_Details\"><h2 class=\"Zocle_Content_Headline\"><a href=\"http://zocle.us/P84w\" target=\"_blank\">JavaScript Daily</a></h2><div class=\"Zocle_Content_URL\">Via&nbsp;twitter.com</div><div class=\"Zocle_Content_Teaser\">How to Use ExpressJS with Node.js to Write Data to A MongoDB Database: <a href=\"http://zocle.us/Q84w\" target=\"_blank\">youtube.com/watch?v=LB32jT…</a> <a href=\"http://zocle.us/R84w\" target=\"_blank\">#video</a></div><div class=\"Zocle_Content_Date\">11/25/2014 10:01 AM</