47','2015-01-27 05:33:47','<div><p>Sometimes you need to change a file in Git and maybe you don\'t want to commit that change.</p><p>So you can do something like this:</p><p><span style=\"color: #FF0000;\">git update-index --assume-unchanged filename<br></span></p><p>If you want to stop ignoring changes in the file, use the following command:<br><span style=\"color: #FF0000;\">git update-index --no-assume-unchanged filename<br></span></p></div>','Temporarily Ignore Changes for a File in Git','','inherit','open','open','','263-revision-v1','','','2015-01-27 00:33:47','2015-01-27 05:33:47','',263,'http://zhexiao.zz.mu/263-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(266,1,'2015-01-27 11:53:48','2015-01-27 16:53:48','<div><p>To install both Sass and Compass in Ubuntu 12.10, Ubuntu 13.04 or Debian you will first need to install ruby and ruby gems packages.<br><br><span style=\"color: #FF0000;\">sudo apt-get install ruby-full rubygems1.8<br></span>Now you can download and install sass and compass with the following commands. (Gem is a package management system for ruby apps think of it as apt-get for ruby)<br><br><span style=\"color: #FF0000;\">sudo gem install sass<br>sudo gem install compass</span></p><p><br></p><p><br><br></p></div>','Install Sass and Compass on ubuntu','','publish','open','open','','install-sass-and-compass-on-ubuntu','','','2015-01-27 11:54:51','2015-01-27 16:54:51','',0,'http://zhexiao.zz.mu/?p=266',0,'post','',0),(267,1,'2015-01-27 11:53:48','2015-01-27 16:53:48','<div><p>To install both Sass and Compass in Ubuntu 12.10, Ubuntu 13.04 or Debian you will first need to install ruby and ruby gems packages.<br><br><span style=\"color: #FF0000;\">sudo apt-get install ruby-full rubygems1.8<br></span>Now you can download and install sass and compass with the following commands. (Gem is a package management system for ruby apps think of it as apt-get for ruby)<br><br><span style=\"color: #FF0000;\">sudo gem install sass<br>sudo gem install compass</span></p><p><br></